ah T. Hawkins]] (J)\n* {{ushr|North Carolina|7|7}}. [[Edmund Deberry]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|North Carolina|8|8}}. [[William Montgomery (North Carolina)|William Montgomery]] (J)\n* {{ushr|North Carolina|9|9}}. [[Augustine Henry Shepperd|Augustine H. Shepperd]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|North Carolina|10|10}}. [[Abraham Rencher]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|North Carolina|11|11}}. [[Henry William Connor|Henry W. Connor]] (J)\n* {{ushr|North Carolina|12|12}}. [[James Graham (NC politician)|James Graham]] (AJ), until March 29, 1836, and from December 5, 1836\n* {{ushr|North Carolina|13|13}}. [[Lewis Williams]] (AJ)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Ohio|Ohio]] ====\n* {{ushr|Ohio|1|1}}. [[Bellamy Storer (1796)|Bellamy Storer]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Ohio|2|2}}. [[Taylor Webster]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Ohio|3|3}}. [[Joseph Halsey Crane|Joseph H. Crane]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Ohio|4|4}}. [[Thomas Corwin]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Ohio|5|5}}. [[Thomas L. Hamer]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Ohio|6|6}}. [[Samuel Finley Vinton|Samuel F. Vinton]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Ohio|7|7}}. [[William K. Bond]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Ohio|8|8}}. [[Jeremiah McLene]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Ohio|9|9}}. [[John Chaney (representative)|John Chaney]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Ohio|10|10}}. [[Samson Mason]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Ohio|11|11}}. [[William Kennon, Sr.]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Ohio|12|12}}. [[Elias Howell]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Ohio|13|13}}. [[David Spangler (representative)|David Spangler]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Ohio|14|14}}. [[William Patterson (Ohio)|William Patterson]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Ohio|15|15}}. [[Jonathan Sloane]] (AM)\n* {{ushr|Ohio|16|16}}. [[Elisha Whittlesey]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Ohio|17|17}}. [[John Thomson (Ohio politician)|John Thomson]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Ohio|18|18}}. [[Benjamin Jones (congressman)|Benjamin Jones]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Ohio|19|19}}. [[Daniel Kilgore (politician)|Daniel Kilgore]] (J)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Pennsylvania|Pennsylvania]] ====\nThere were two plural districts, the 2nd had two representatives, the 4th had three representatives.\n* {{ushr|Pennsylvania|