liam Herod]] (AJ), from January 25, 1837\n* {{ushr|Indiana|7|7}}. [[Edward A. Hannegan]] (J)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Kentucky|Kentucky]] ====\n* {{ushr|Kentucky|1|1}}. [[Linn Boyd]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Kentucky|2|2}}. [[Albert G. Hawes]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Kentucky|3|3}}. [[Joseph R. Underwood]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Kentucky|4|4}}. [[Sherrod Williams]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Kentucky|5|5}}. [[James Harlan (congressman)|James Harlan]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Kentucky|6|6}}. [[John Calhoon]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Kentucky|7|7}}. [[Benjamin Hardin]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Kentucky|8|8}}. [[William J. Graves]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Kentucky|9|9}}. [[John White (Kentucky politician)|John White]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Kentucky|10|10}}. [[Chilton Allan]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Kentucky|11|11}}. [[Richard French (US politician)|Richard French]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Kentucky|12|12}}. [[John Chambers (Kentucky)|John Chambers]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Kentucky|13|13}}. [[Richard Mentor Johnson|Richard M. Johnson]] (J)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Louisiana|Louisiana]] ====\n* {{ushr|Louisiana|1|1}}. [[Henry Johnson (Louisiana)|Henry Johnson]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Louisiana|2|2}}. [[Eleazar W. Ripley]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Louisiana|3|3}}. [[Rice Garland]] (AJ)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Maine|Maine]] ====\n* {{ushr|Maine|1|1}}. [[John Fairfield]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Maine|2|2}}. [[Francis Ormand Jonathan Smith|Francis O. J. Smith]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Maine|3|3}}. [[Jeremiah Bailey]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Maine|4|4}}. [[George Evans (American politician)|George Evans]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Maine|5|5}}. [[Moses Mason, Jr.]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Maine|6|6}}. [[Leonard Jarvis]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Maine|7|7}}. [[Joseph Hall (Maine)|Joseph Hall]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Maine|8|8}}. [[Gorham Parks]] (J)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Maryland|Maryland]] ====\nThe 4th district was a plural district with two representatives.\n* {{ushr|Maryland|1|1}}. [[John Nevett Steele|John N. Steele]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Maryland|2|2}}. [[James Pearce|James A. Pearce]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Maryland|3|3}}. [[James Turner (Maryland)|James Turner]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Maryland|4|4}}. [[Benjamin Chew Howard|Benjamin C. Howard]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Maryland|4|4}}. [[Isaac McKim]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Maryland|5|5}}. [[George Corbin Washington|George C. Washington]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Maryland|6|6}}. [[Francis Thomas]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Maryland|7|7}}. [[Daniel Jenifer]] (AJ)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Massachusetts|Massachusetts]] ====\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|1|1}}. [[Abbott Lawrence]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|2|2}}. [[Stephen C. Phillips]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|3|3}}. [[Caleb Cushing]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|4|4}}. [[Samuel Hoar]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|5|5}}. [[Levi Lincoln, Jr.]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|6|6}}. [[George Grennell, Jr.|George J. Grennell, Jr.]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|7|7}}. [[George N. Briggs]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|8|8}}. [[William B. Calhoun]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|9|9}}. [[William Jackson (Massachusetts politician, born 1783)|William Jackson]] (AM)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|10|10}}. [[Nathaniel B. Borden]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|11|11}}. [[John Reed, Jr.]] (AM)\n* {{ushr|Massachusetts|12|12}}. [[John Quincy Adams]] (AM)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Michigan|Michigan]] ====\n* {{ushr|Michigan|AL|At-large}}. [[Isaac E. Crary]] (J), from January 26, 1837 (newly admitted state)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Mississippi|Mississippi]] ====\nBoth representatives were elected statewide on a [[general ticket]].\n* {{ushr|Mississippi|AL|At-large}}. [[John Francis Hamtramck Claiborne|John F. H. Claiborne]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Mississippi|AL|At-large}}. [[David Dickson (politician)|David Dickson]] (AJ), until July 31, 1836\n** [[Samuel J. Gholson]] (J), from December 1, 1836\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Missouri|Missouri]] ====\nBoth representatives were elected statewide on a [[general ticket]].\n