arolina|8|8}}. [[James Blair (South Carolina)|James Blair]] (J), until April 1, 1834\n** [[Richard Irvine Manning I|Richard I. Manning]] (J), from December 8, 1834\n* {{ushr|South Carolina|9|9}}. [[John K. Griffin]] ([[Nullifier Party|N]])\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Tennessee|Tennessee]] ====\n* {{ushr|Tennessee|1|1}}. [[John Blair (Tennessee)|John Blair]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Tennessee|2|2}}. [[Samuel Bunch]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Tennessee|3|3}}. [[Luke Lea (1783-1851)|Luke Lea]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Tennessee|4|4}}. [[James Israel Standifer|James I. Standifer]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Tennessee|5|5}}. [[John B. Forester]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Tennessee|6|6}}. [[Balie Peyton]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Tennessee|7|7}}. [[John Bell (Tennessee politician)|John Bell]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Tennessee|8|8}}. [[David W. Dickinson]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Tennessee|9|9}}. [[James K. Polk]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Tennessee|10|10}}. [[William Marshall Inge|William M. Inge]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Tennessee|11|11}}. [[Cave Johnson]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Tennessee|12|12}}. [[Davy Crockett|David Crockett]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Tennessee|13|13}}. [[William Claiborne Dunlap|William C. Dunlap]] (J)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Vermont|Vermont]] ====\n* {{ushr|Vermont|1|1}}. [[Hiland Hall]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Vermont|2|2}}. [[William Slade]] (AM)\n* {{ushr|Vermont|3|3}}. [[Horace Everett]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Vermont|4|4}}. [[Heman Allen (Milton)|Heman Allen]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Vermont|5|5}}. [[Benjamin F. Deming]] (AM), until July 11, 1834\n** [[Henry F. Janes]] (AM), from December 2, 1834\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Virginia|Virginia]] ====\n* {{ushr|Virginia|1|1}}. [[George Loyall]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Virginia|2|2}}. [[John Y. Mason]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Virginia|3|3}}. [[William S. Archer]] (J)\n* {{ushr|Virginia|4|4}}. [[James Gholson|James H. Gholson]] (AJ)\n* {{ushr|Virginia|5|5}}. [[John Randolph of Roanoke|John Randolph]] (J), until May 24, 1833\n** [[Thomas T. Bouldin]] (J), from December 2, 1833, until February 11,