 White]] (AJ)\n| Resigned November 15, 1834, to become [[Governor of Louisiana]]\n| {{party shading/Anti-Jacksonian}} | [[Henry Johnson (Louisiana)|Henry Johnson]] (AJ)\n| Seated December 1, 1834\n|-\n| {{ushr|Georgia|AL|Georgia At-large}}\n| {{party shading/Jacksonian}} | [[James Moore Wayne|James M. Wayne]] (J)\n| Resigned January 13, 1835, after being appointed an Associate Justice of the [[United States Supreme Court]]\n| colspan=2 rowspan=2 | Not filled in this Congress\n|-\n| {{ushr|South Carolina|6|South Carolina 6th}}\n| {{party shading/Nullifier}} | [[Warren R. Davis]] ([[Nullifier Party|N]])\n| Died January 29, 1835\n|}\n\n==Committees==\nLists of committees and their party leaders.\n\n===Senate===\n\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Agriculture|Agriculture]] (Chairman: [[Bedford Brown]])\n* [[United States Senate Select Committee on Amendments to the Constitution|Amendments to the Constitution]] (Select)\n* [[United States Senate Committee to Audit and Control the Contingent Expenses of the Senate|Audit and Control the Contingent Expenses of the Senate]] (Chairman: [[Nehemiah Knight]])\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Claims|Claims]] (Chairman: [[Samuel Bell]])\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Commerce|Commerce]] (Chairman: [[Nathaniel Silsbee]])\n* [[United States Senate Select Committee on Distributing Public Revenue Among the States|Distributing Public Revenue Among the States]] (Select)\n* [[United States Senate Committee on the District of Columbia|District of Columbia]] (Chairman: [[Ezekiel F. Chambers]] then [[John Tyler]])\n* [[United States Senate Select Committee on Establishing Branches of the Mint|Establishing Branches of the Mint]] (Select)\n* [[United States Senate Select Committee on the Executive Patronage|Executive Patronage]] (Select)\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Finance|Finance]] (Chairman: [[Daniel Webster]])\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Foreign Relations|Foreign Relations]] (Chairman: [[William Wilkins (U.S. politician)|William Wilkins]] then [[Henry Clay]])\n* [[United States Senate Select Committee on French Spoilations|French Spoilations]] (Select)\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Indian Affairs|Indian Affairs]] (Chairman: [[Hugh Lawson White]])\n* [[United States Senate Committee on the Judiciary|Judiciary]] (Chairman: [[John M. Clayton]]) \n* [[United States Senate Committee on Manufactures|Manufactures]] (Chairman: N/A)\n* [[United States Senate Select Committee on the Michigan and Arkansas Admission to the Union|Michigan and Arkansas Admission to the Union]] (Select)\n* [[United States Senate Select Committee on the Mileage of Members of Congress|Mileage of Members of Congress]] (Select)\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Military Affairs|Military Affairs]] (Chairman: [[Nathaniel Silsbee]])\n* [[United States Senate Committee on the Militia|Militia]] (Chairman: N/A)\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Naval Affairs|Naval Affairs]] (Chairman: [[Samuel Southard]])\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Pensions|Pensions]] (Chairman: N/A)\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Post Office and Post Roads|Post Office and Post Roads]] (Chairman: N/A)\n* [[United States Senate Select Committee on President's Message Refusing to Furnish a Paper to Senate|President's Message Refusing to Furnish a Paper to Senate]] (Select)\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Private Land Claims|Private Land Claims]] (Chairman: N/A)\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Public Lands|Public Lands]] (Chairman: [[George Poindexter]])\n* [[United States Senate Select Committee on Purchasing Boyd Reilly's Gas Apparatus|Purchasing Boyd Reilly's Gas Apparatus]] (Select)\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Revolutionary Claims|Revolutionary Claims]] (Chairman: N/A)\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Roads and Canals|Roads and Canals]] (Chairman: N/A)\n* [[United States Senate Select Committee on Shiloh National Park|Shiloh National Park]] (Select)\n* [[United Sta